EU Lifts Deadline On Google Inc., Motorola Mobility Holdings Inc. Deal-Reuters
Monday, 12 Dec 2011 11:14pm EST
Reuters reported that EU regulators have suspended a January 10 deadline for a decision on Google Inc.'s bid to buy Motorola Mobility Holdings Inc. as it waits for the Company to provide more information on the deal. The deadline is suspended because the (European) Commission needs from Google certain documents that are essential to its evaluation of the transaction. Once the Commission has all the necessary information, it will re-start the clock and publish a new Phase I deadline on the website. Google, which announced the $12.5 billion deal in August. The Commission has asked rivals and users for feedback on the deal. According to questionnaires sent earlier this month, the regulator asked whether Google would favour Motorola Mobility over other hardware manufacturers that license Google's software. U.S. antitrust regulators are also reviewing the deal.Â 
